Listening to this wonderful book called <a href="http://www.books24x7.com/toc.aspx?bookid=46967">The Power of Habit</a> by <a href="http://charlesduhigg.com">Charles Duhigg</a> [book title links to the audio book on Books 24x7 that should be accessible to all of us for free].

Would recommend this book as it talks about some very powerful concepts around how habits are formed and how to change them in individuals, teams and societies.

&nbsp;

The core idea of the book is what the author calls the habit loop a pattern that our brain learns and remembers for a long time if the reward leads to a feeling of craving

(proven by neuro-science research covered in the book).

The habit loop is characterized by 3 things a cue, a routine and a reward. When this is repeated multiple times we start doing it without putting too much thought thus becoming a habit.

Hacking this loop can help get rid of bad habits (e.g. smoking) as well inculcating good one (e.g. exercising)

