At least thinking of ...

Looking to learn the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/dvorak">dvorak </a>layout for typing on my laptop. <a href="http://windows.microsoft.com/en-in/windows/change-keyboard-layout#1TC=windows-7">Configured the keyboard layout</a> to have the option to switch between qwerty and dvorak. Apparently the dvorak layout saves time and effort (and hence reduces chances of injuries such as CTS) while typing. Heard about it in a podcast interview with the founder of wordpress who has made it mandatory for all employees at this company (Automattic).

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

Heard this beautiful <a href="http://www.ted.com/talks/ricardo_semler_radical_wisdom_for_a_company_a_school_a_life">TED talk</a> by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ricardo_Semler">Ricardo Semler</a> today. He started off by saying that Monday's and Thursday's are called terminal days in his schedule. On these 2 days in the week, he works on he really wants to - knocking off his bucket list. As many of his immediate family members died of cancer, he introduced this into his life so that he need not postpone things he loves to do to the end.

Wonderfully radical ideas on how to build companies with the core idea being to relinquish control ! He applied this concept to education and has started a very different kind of school called the <a href="http://lumiar.org.br/?lang=en">Lumiar School</a>. A must watch/listen talk if you are interested in radical concepts.

